cs.CV, cs.GR, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.RO

The paper deals with image classification using convolutional neural networks, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The use of multi-view projections and depth planes suggests a focus on 3D scene understanding, which falls under graphics (cs.GR). The paper also mentions the creation of a training set using manually-created polygons on a map, which suggests a focus on machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the application of the method to aerial imagery suggests a focus on robotics (cs.RO) and remote sensing.
